-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/daewoo-shipbuilding-pipavav-tata-tele-asia-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Asian trading on May 7. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices are as of the latest close.
The information in each item was released after markets shut
unless stated otherwise.  Daewoo Shipbuilding & Marine Engineering Co. (042660)  (042660 KS):
The company said it received a 1.25 trillion won ($1.1 billion)
order for oil rigs, according to a regulatory filing. The
shipbuilder was unchanged at 31,600 won.  Pipavav Defence and Offshore Engineering Co . (PIPV IN):
Life Insurance Corp. of  India , the largest insurer, bought 25.5
million more shares in the shipyard, raising its stake to 8.74
percent, according to an exchange filing. Pipavav shares sank
3.1 percent to 84.05 rupees.  StarHub Ltd. (STH)  : Singaporeâ€™s second-biggest mobile-
phone carrier said first-quarter net income climbed 28 percent
from a year earlier to S$88.4 million ($72 million). That beat
the S$79.8 million average estimate of four analysts compiled by
Bloomberg News.  Tata Teleservices Maharashtra Ltd. (TTLS)  : The Indian
company posted a fourth-quarter loss of 1.23 billion rupees,
compared with a loss of 3.3 billion rupees last year. The
median estimate in a Bloomberg News survey of three analysts
was for a loss of 1.36 billion rupees. Shares slid 1.1 percent
to 13.3 rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
